
@startuml

' Define classes
class User {
    - username: String (unique)
    - password: String
}

class Player {
    + playGame(game: Game): void
    + pauseGame(): void
    + resumeGame(): void
}

class Admin {
    + createGame(): Game
    + designGame(game: Game): void
}

class Game {
    - name: String (unique)
    - hallOfFame: HallOfFame
    - blocks: List<Block>
    - levels: List<Level>
    - minSpeed: int
    - speedIncreaseFactor: float
    - maxLength: int
    - minLength: int
    - admin: Admin
}

class Block {
    - color: String
    - points: int (1-1000)
}

class Level {
    - number: int (1-99)
    - gridLayout: Map<String, Block>  // e.g., "1/1": Block
    - isRandom: boolean
    - blockCount: int
}

class HallOfFame {
    - entries: List<ScoreEntry>
}

class ScoreEntry {
    - player: Player
    - score: int
    - date: Date
}

class GameSession {
    - player: Player
    - game: Game
    - currentLevel: int
    - lives: int
    - totalScore: int
    - paused: boolean
}

' Inheritance
User <|-- Player
User <|-- Admin

' Associations
Admin --> Game : creates
Game --> Admin : has one admin
Game --> Block : defines
Game --> Level : contains
Game --> HallOfFame : has
Level --> Block : uses
Player --> GameSession : participates in
Game --> GameSession : played by
GameSession --> Level : plays
GameSession --> Player : belongs to
HallOfFame --> ScoreEntry : records
ScoreEntry --> Player : achieved by

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- **User** is the base class that can be either a **Player** or an **Admin**.
- A **Game** is created by an **Admin**, who also defines its **Blocks** and **Levels**.
- Each **Game** has its own **Hall of Fame**, which stores **ScoreEntry** objects.
- A **Player** interacts with a **GameSession**, which tracks progress like current level, lives, and score.
- The **GameSession** allows pausing/resuming and ensures only one game is active at a time per player.
- The **Level** includes a grid layout and may be randomized.

